heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 10.1mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 10th in our overall records.  The storm lasted 16.6 hours and 9.37mm of rain fell.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: Today, one rain storm lasted for 16.6 hours (ranking 10th for longest storm from our records).  It accumulated 9.37mm of rain and it fell at 10.1mm per hour at times.  A relentless rainstorm took place on 04 January 2025, it lasted 37.2 hours and it delivered 36.8mm of rain at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.
